The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech in Seoul, South Korea, reaffirming the country's commitment to its alliance with South Korea and addressing the threat posed by North Korea. Pence stated that the United States stands with South Korea "100 percent" and that the alliance between the two countries is crucial for peace and security in the region. He also discussed the economic partnership between the US and South Korea, expressing concern about the growing trade deficit and the need to address barriers to entry for American businesses. Pence reassured the audience that the Trump administration is working to pass an aggressive agenda to stimulate the American economy, including tax reform and reducing regulations. He concluded his speech by emphasizing the shared sacrifice and values between the US and South Korea and the enduring bond between the two nations.